column5: i know this has been discussed in another thread along time ago but can anybody recommend a motel in pickle lake? thanks, phish
Bob, E-mail Tim at [email protected] he has motel info for pickle lake Larry

thanks, larry. are you guys staying in pickle for your trip in june? we're planning on arriving the evening before in hopes of flying out very early the next morning. i recall a thread a few years ago about how bad motels were in pickle and wonder if things are any better. later, bob

we are staying at winston motor inn-stayed there 10 years ago and it was very nice.cant find phone number right now.do a google search for pickle lake and it will be there.what lake and outfitter are you going to.have a nice trip,tim
Here's a listing of all available lodging in Pickle Lake.http://www.picklelake.ca/directory_items.asp?id=18
hey tim - i'll be at kecheokagan two weeks after you!! can't wait to hear how you do. phishfearme=bob kerr
Unless things have changed since I was stationed there on teh DNR base, the Central Pat (Central Patricia Hotel) is the only motel in town.
Never mind, I guess the little gold mine town has a couple more.... See the website listed in the post above.
